text: Reetta Sofi Kaarina Hurske (born 15 May 1995) is a Finnish athlete specialising in the sprint hurdles. She represented her country at the 2018 World Indoor Championships reaching the semifinals. At the 2019 European Indoor Championships Hurske placed 4th. Her personal bests are 12.78 seconds in the 100 metres hurdles (+1.3 m/s, Joensuu 2019) and 7.97 seconds in the 60 metres hurdles (Kuopio 2019). With the latter she is a joint Finnish record holder together with Nooralotta Neziri.
